<section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 md:px-6">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Upherds Lane</h1>

  <div class="prose-page mt-6">
    <p>
      Upherds is a smaller site than New Barns, with about 45 tenants. The site is triangular with
      mostly small plots which are subdivisions of the original 10 pole plot layout. The ground
      slopes gently from the south-western boundary with the houses in West Fen Road down to Upherds
      Lane. Soil has a clay content as this is on the original Isle of Ely. Mains water is available
      on site, parking on adjacent street.<br />
      The major site paths were relaid during the 2016/17 winter when the water pipes were installed,
      providing wide and firm access to most parts of the site.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/uploads/1/1/7/0/117060630/upherds_allotments_plan_feb20.pdf" target="_blank">Download a site plan of the arcane plot numbers here.</a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <iframe
    class="h-[400px] w-full rounded-lg my-6"
    loading="lazy"
    src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=52.4024143,0.2560077000000547&z=16&output=embed"
    title="Map of Upherds Lane"
  ></iframe>
  <p class="text-sm text-brand-ink/70">Note: map marker position is indicative only</p>
</section>

